BusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: Catholic Youth Organization of the Archdiocese of Indianapolis Inc

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: The Catholic Youth Organization exists to provide opportunities for youth to develop strong moral character, self worth, and a community service orientation through activities of a social, educational and recreational nature, based on Catholic principles that reinforce proper social values. As a community of faith within the Archdiocese of Indianapolis, the CYO is committed to a ministry of formation that helps bring youth to their full human potential.

IRS990.Desc: YOUTH ATHLETICS - CYO YOUTH ATHLETICS PROGRAMS ARE OFFERED TO PARISH YOUTH AGES 9 TO 18 YEARS. SPORTS INCLUDE BOYS BASKETBALL, GIRLS BASKETBALL, FOOTBALL, GIRLS VOLLEYBALL, BOYS VOLLEYBALL, SPRING AND FALL KICKBALL, WRESTLING, CO-ED SOCCER, BASEBALL, SOFTBALL AND BOYS AND GIRLS TRACK. THESE PROGRAMS ARE DESIGNED TO PROVIDE YOUTH THE OPPORTUNITY TO PURSUE THE AIMS OF CHARACTER DEVELOPMENT, SELF-WORTH, TEAM BUILDING, AND PERSONAL FITNESS. OVER 15,000 YOUTH SERVED THROUGH 49 PARISHES/SCHOOLS IN CENTRAL INDIANA.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: ENRICHMENT PROGRAMS INCLUDE A REGION-WIDE MUSIC CONTEST WITH HONORS RECITAL, AND CHESS CLUB.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: SUPPORT OF CYO CAMP RANCHO FRAMASA. DURING FY 22-23, CYO FORGAVE AN INTERCOMPANY PAYABLE/RECEIVABLE BALANCE OWED BY CYO CAMP RANCHO FRAMASA FOR $170,527. THIS TRANSACTION IS REFLECTED AS A GRANT TO A DOMESTIC ORGANIZATION ON PART IX.
